Package com.github.dscpsyl.jgrade2

Class CLITester

java.lang.Object
com.github.dscpsyl.jgrade2.CLITester
public abstract class CLITester extends Object
A class to assist in testing the main method of programs that are designed with a command line interface (as many introductory assignments are). The public static methods can be used to assist in getting output, or a class can extend this class, set the invocation, and build unit tests around it to test functionality via JUnit.

  • Method Details

    • getInvocation

      protected abstract List<String> getInvocation()
      Get the invocation for the CLI program. initCommand() (which is annotated with @Before) calls this method to set the command. Subclasses implement this method to tell it how to setup the command. For example, if a user had main program Hello, they may do the following to implement this method: return Arrays.asList(new String[] {"java", "-cp", "lib/:.", "Hello"});
      Returns:
      The List of Strings that would invoke the program.

    • initCommand

      @BeforeEach public void initCommand()
      Initializes the command for the test (and is annotated with BeforeEach. Calls the abstract getInvocation() and initializes a new ProcessBuilder.

    • getCommand

      public List<String> getCommand()
      Get the command that was initialized from initCommand(). If adding command line arguments, call this method and append to the command the arguments. For example, in a specific method the user could do getCommand().append("arg1"); before calling runCommand().
      Returns:
      The current command (which is a List of Strings).

    • addCommandLineArg

      public void addCommandLineArg(String s)
      Add a command line argument to the command to be run.
      Parameters:
      s - The command line argument to be added

    • getBuilder

      public ProcessBuilder getBuilder()
      Get the ProcessBuilder that was initialized from initCommand(). If wanting to edit things about the builder for instance ProcessBuilder.redirectErrorStream() use this method to access the builder.
      Returns:
      The ProcessBuilder being used.

    • setPrintOutput

      public void setPrintOutput(boolean to)
      Set whether or not to print the captured output. If true, then when runCommand() is called it will automatically print the output to System.out.
      Parameters:
      to - The boolean value to set whether or not to print output.

    • runCommand

      protected CLIResult runCommand(String withInput)

      Parameters:

    • runCommand

      protected CLIResult runCommand()
      Run the command as it is currently set for this class without feeding in anything to stdin. If the program takes command line input, see runCommand(String).
      Returns:
      The result of the execution of the program.

    • executeProcess

      public static CLIResult executeProcess(ProcessBuilder builder, String toWriteIn)
      Execute a process provided a ProcessBuilder that has a command set to invoke the process, and a String for input to feed to the program.
      Parameters:
      builder - The ProcessBuilder to use for the command.
      toWriteIn - Input for the program that it reads from stdin.
      Returns:
      The CLIResult containing the output from the run.

    • executeProcess

      public static CLIResult executeProcess(ProcessBuilder builder)
      Executes a process with a provided ProcessBuilder but sends no input to the program. Other than that, same as executeProcess(ProcessBuilder, String).
      Parameters:
      builder - The ProcessBuilder to use to run.
      Returns:
      The CLIResult containing the output from the run.
